pretation alone cannot do justice to the dimension of "presence," a dimension in which cultural phenomena and cultural events become tangible and have an impact on our senses and our bodies. Production of Presence is a passionate plea for a rethinking and a reshaping of the intellectual practice within the humanities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aAesthetics. 0aExperience. 4aLiterary Studies -- General Criticism and Theory. 4aPhilosophy -- Poststructuralism and Phenomenology. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Semiotics & Theory.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080476714940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804767149423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804767149/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles